Feature Scaling

It is a technique to standardize the independent features in a data in a fixed range or scale

What it does is keep the distribution of the data, the correlation and covariance absolutely the same however scales every independent or the feature matrix columns to a smaller scale. We do this as most of the ML algorithms problems perform significantly better after scaling.

1. Standardization:

Standardization is a scaling technique where the values are centered around the mean with a unit standard deviation. This means that the mean of the attribute becomes zero and the resultant distribution has a unit standard deviation.
